All in all, pretty enjoyable and well-written. The clinical tone could use a tiny bit of touching-up(mostly just at the term  I would try to find a different term) but overall really well written.

As a Louisiana resident, the  part threw me for a bit of a loop at first. Having an entire town in my home state wiped from existence is a really interesting concept, though the potentially worldwide scale of Amnestics that would need to be administered to make anyone who has ever heard of it forget about an entire town is kind of difficult to wrap my head around. Maybe a bit about using experimental memetic amnestic agents would help?







